WEBVTT

00:06.506 --> 00:08.425
[opening theme music playing]

00:49.299 --> 00:51.968
STILL SHINING

00:53.595 --> 00:54.721
[woman] Tae-seo.

00:58.224 --> 01:00.477
-[bicycle bell rings]
-[gentle music playing]

01:03.688 --> 01:05.231
[Tae-seo] <i>The people you long to see</i>

01:05.857 --> 01:07.317
<i>never appear in your dreams.</i>

01:11.237 --> 01:12.447
[Eun-a] Tae-seo.

01:21.122 --> 01:22.123
[Tae-seo] <i>So…</i>

01:22.874 --> 01:23.958
<i>this isn't a dream.</i>

01:26.086 --> 01:27.128
<i>She'd never appear in one.</i>

01:33.760 --> 01:35.762
[sighs]

01:48.566 --> 01:50.568
[music fades]

01:58.910 --> 01:59.911
[exhales]

02:02.914 --> 02:05.625
-[digital beeps, dings]
-[door opens]

02:08.962 --> 02:09.963
[door closes]

02:11.005 --> 02:12.340
-[door locks]
-[digital beeps]

02:18.138 --> 02:19.472
You're up.

02:19.556 --> 02:21.266
-[plastic rustling]
-Uh…

02:22.016 --> 02:24.227
I found a place that was open
this early in the morning.

02:25.687 --> 02:28.481
These were leftovers from yesterday.
The mushy ones were even cheaper.

02:29.149 --> 02:30.692
You should blend these.

02:30.775 --> 02:32.193
Wait, you don't have a blender.

02:32.277 --> 02:33.736
You should cut out the bad bits.

02:33.820 --> 02:35.780
You didn't have food waste bags either.

02:35.864 --> 02:37.198
You should buy some…

02:41.494 --> 02:42.829
Stop staring.

02:48.168 --> 02:50.170
[pleasant music playing]

02:53.882 --> 02:54.883
[bathroom door closes]

02:56.676 --> 02:57.677
[chuckles softly]

03:27.457 --> 03:28.666
Want some grapes?

03:29.500 --> 03:31.377
I washed the ones that were still decent.

03:37.926 --> 03:38.760
Have one.

03:39.302 --> 03:41.429
Uh, it must be sour after brushing.

03:43.973 --> 03:44.807
It's good.

03:44.891 --> 03:45.892
[chuckles softly]

03:51.898 --> 03:53.900
[music fades]

03:53.983 --> 03:55.360
Why didn't you wake me up?

03:57.862 --> 03:59.155
When do you get off work?

03:59.239 --> 04:01.241
At 6:00 p.m. You should've woken me up.

04:02.575 --> 04:04.244
We could've stayed up all night together.

04:06.246 --> 04:07.956
From now on, I'm going to be in Seoul

04:08.790 --> 04:11.125
managing an old guesthouse,

04:11.209 --> 04:13.336
so we can meet up for a bit after work.

04:14.879 --> 04:16.256
We live close by now.

04:22.512 --> 04:23.596
Take care.

04:36.317 --> 04:38.111
-Bye.
-Okay, bye.

04:47.370 --> 04:49.747
[slow romantic music builds]

04:53.876 --> 04:54.877
[sighs]

05:01.342 --> 05:03.344
[slow romantic music plays]

05:23.156 --> 05:30.121
STILL SHINING

05:34.250 --> 05:35.501
[music continues playing]

05:35.585 --> 05:38.713
[Tae-seo over PA] <i>Due to the morning</i>
<i>commute, the train is very crowded.</i>

05:38.796 --> 05:40.256
<i>Please be considerate of others.</i>

05:41.549 --> 05:43.926
<i>We hope that somewhere today, joy</i>…

05:47.013 --> 05:50.808
[hesitates] …something that
brings you joy awaits you.

05:50.892 --> 05:52.226
-Thank you.
-[button clicks]

05:56.773 --> 05:59.734
[man] Hey, look at the compliments
coming in about Yeon Tae-seo.

05:59.817 --> 06:02.153
-[woman exclaims, chuckles]
-[man] Five, six.

06:02.236 --> 06:03.654
What did he say?

06:03.738 --> 06:07.033
"I hope something
that brings you joy awaits you."

06:07.116 --> 06:08.451
I like that! Right?

06:08.534 --> 06:10.078
[woman] He only ever says the train is

06:10.161 --> 06:12.413
-"Coming to a stop" or "Departing." Hey!
-[man chuckling]

06:12.997 --> 06:14.957
-Yes?
-What did you say today?

06:16.751 --> 06:19.754
Nothing much. Have a good one.

06:19.837 --> 06:21.297
[man] I hope you find joy too.

06:21.380 --> 06:22.840
-Right, you too.
-[man laughs]

06:22.924 --> 06:24.926
[slow romantic music continues playing]

07:00.586 --> 07:01.504
[Eun-a] Tae-seo.

07:16.394 --> 07:17.353
Shall we go?

07:26.446 --> 07:28.364
-[Eun-a] Wow!
-[music fades]

07:28.448 --> 07:31.075
[Tae-seo]
I heard this is a famous photo spot.

07:39.667 --> 07:41.127
[camera shutter clicks]

07:43.754 --> 07:45.339
[Tae-seo clears throat, sniffles]

07:46.591 --> 07:48.050
-[Tae-seo sniffles]
-Yeon Namsan.

07:50.970 --> 07:54.265
It's okay for you to face me now.

07:57.393 --> 07:59.562
[chuckles] This can't be real.

08:01.147 --> 08:03.107
It feels like a dream.

08:03.191 --> 08:04.692
[inhales]

08:04.775 --> 08:06.777
-[gentle music playing]
-[Tae-seo exhales]

08:08.529 --> 08:09.405
[inhales sharply]

08:09.489 --> 08:13.034
Do you want to walk a bit further?
Or want to take more photos here?

08:14.452 --> 08:15.703
Let's go a bit further.

08:23.336 --> 08:25.338
[music continues playing]

08:39.519 --> 08:42.522
[Eun-a] <i>I dropped by a photo store</i>
<i>on my way home and had it developed.</i>

08:44.357 --> 08:45.650
<i>Good night, Tae-seo.</i>

08:49.862 --> 08:51.864
[music fades]

08:52.490 --> 08:55.785
I'll put these in the wash
at the laundromat on my way home.

08:56.911 --> 08:59.872
Please put them in the dryer later,
and then bring them back here.

08:59.956 --> 09:03.000
You'll have to make two trips.

09:03.084 --> 09:05.002
I didn't hear anything about a laundromat.

09:05.086 --> 09:10.132
I was told a professional laundry service
picks them up and brings them back.

09:10.216 --> 09:11.092
They used to.

09:13.844 --> 09:15.471
They quit a month ago.

09:15.555 --> 09:19.058
The boss said he'd look for another one,
but who knows if he is.

09:40.496 --> 09:42.498
I should eat a hearty meal
and keep my energy up.

09:45.042 --> 09:47.044
[gentle music playing]

09:51.882 --> 09:52.925
Mmm…

09:57.638 --> 09:59.432
[digital beeping]

09:59.515 --> 10:03.394
PAYMENT COMPLETE

10:09.066 --> 10:10.192
[cellphone vibrates]

10:12.320 --> 10:13.988
[Tae-seo] <i>I'll come see you at work.</i>

10:17.950 --> 10:19.243
At work…

10:23.289 --> 10:26.667
<i>If I stop by Unit 203 after work,</i>
<i>it'll be around the time you get off.</i>

10:27.168 --> 10:28.461
<i>I'll come to you.</i>

10:29.545 --> 10:31.464
<i>I want to spend a day in your shoes.</i>

10:32.006 --> 10:33.883
<i>All the things you see every day in Seoul,</i>

10:34.467 --> 10:35.301
<i>I want to see too.</i>

10:35.384 --> 10:38.971
DONGJAK STATION EXIT 2

10:43.309 --> 10:45.311
[music fades]

10:51.317 --> 10:52.318
Mo Eun-a.

11:03.454 --> 11:04.664
[clears throat] Uh…

11:05.414 --> 11:07.124
-Can I ask something?
-Sure.

11:07.875 --> 11:09.752
Will you be staying in Unit 203?

11:10.795 --> 11:12.004
Just for the time being.

11:12.505 --> 11:15.466
They felt bad and let me
have the house for two weeks. Mmm…

11:16.050 --> 11:17.343
And I found a place to live.

11:17.426 --> 11:20.304
It's where the previous manager lived.
The dates work out perfectly.

11:20.388 --> 11:21.639
The Monday after next.

11:22.306 --> 11:24.100
Are you free then? Anytime in the evening?

11:24.934 --> 11:26.310
Hold on, I'll check.

11:26.394 --> 11:28.187
I'm going to have a small party that day.

11:28.813 --> 11:31.232
My roommate, you, and me.

11:31.315 --> 11:33.067
The three of us. Nothing fancy.

11:33.776 --> 11:35.194
The start of my life in Seoul.

11:38.906 --> 11:40.074
I can make it.

11:40.574 --> 11:41.951
-[Eun-a giggles]
-[Tae-seo inhales]

11:42.034 --> 11:45.037
[sighs deeply] It won't be easy
to follow my daily routine.

11:45.121 --> 11:45.955
[Eun-a chuckles]

11:48.082 --> 11:49.417
-What are you doing?
-What?

11:50.042 --> 11:51.293
Do I need a full warm-up?

11:51.377 --> 11:54.338
[chuckling] No, we're going to run.
Why are you only warming up your hands?

11:54.964 --> 11:56.465
Come on, do your legs too.

11:56.549 --> 11:58.134
[pleasant music playing]

11:58.217 --> 11:59.593
One, two.

12:01.554 --> 12:03.139
Three, four.

12:04.098 --> 12:04.932
The other side.

12:09.019 --> 12:11.939
[Eun-a groaning, panting]

12:12.022 --> 12:13.107
I'm exhausted.

12:14.150 --> 12:15.359
Let's take a break.

12:17.069 --> 12:19.155
-[Tae-seo] Are you okay?
-[Eun-a breathing heavily]

12:22.324 --> 12:23.159
Wow.

12:23.826 --> 12:26.454
So you see this every day
on your way home.

12:26.537 --> 12:29.373
[gasps] You'd have a great view
of the fireworks festival.

12:29.457 --> 12:32.168
I was always so jealous
when Seoul would hold fireworks festivals.

12:32.251 --> 12:33.502
It's right there.

12:35.296 --> 12:37.548
[chuckles softly] That way.

12:37.631 --> 12:38.757
It's that way.

12:38.841 --> 12:41.635
[Eun-a] Ah… So that's Yeouido.

12:43.721 --> 12:46.515
-Where's your energy?
-[chuckling]

12:50.019 --> 12:50.978
So…

12:52.438 --> 12:56.442
I don't know many restaurants
or any good food spots,

12:56.525 --> 12:58.194
but this one's the best place I've tried,

12:58.903 --> 13:01.489
and the food's high in protein.

13:02.239 --> 13:03.949
There's one thing
I'm worried about though.

13:04.658 --> 13:05.701
[chuckles]

13:06.702 --> 13:07.912
He's here.

13:11.332 --> 13:12.166
[exhales]

13:12.708 --> 13:13.834
[Hyeong-seok exclaims]

13:15.419 --> 13:18.130
You're both acting so shocked.

13:18.214 --> 13:20.174
[Hyeong-seok]
How could I not be shocked by this?

13:20.257 --> 13:23.636
[exclaims] I've never seen Yeon Tae-seo
hang out with anyone else.

13:23.719 --> 13:24.637
Right.

13:24.720 --> 13:27.473
Yeon Tae-seo's always alone.
He'd always been studying by himself.

13:28.140 --> 13:29.391
He has no friends.

13:29.475 --> 13:32.895
Geez, were you like that over there too?
Boring, like eating rice with no meat?

13:34.021 --> 13:35.356
Ma'am!

13:36.190 --> 13:37.525
-Soju?
-You bet.

13:38.025 --> 13:40.569
-Ma'am, I'm taking a bottle of soju!
-[woman] Okay.

13:40.653 --> 13:42.655
[amusing music playing]

13:43.155 --> 13:45.032
[Eun-a] Did Tae-seo ever mention me?

13:45.115 --> 13:46.742
-Your name is…
-Mo Eun-a.

13:46.825 --> 13:48.786
He bad-mouthed me, right? What did he say?

13:48.869 --> 13:51.455
Come on, why does that matter?
The present is what counts.

13:52.081 --> 13:53.082
You don't know who I am.

13:53.707 --> 13:55.292
Right, today's the first time…

13:56.043 --> 13:58.212
[exclaims] Actually, no!

13:58.295 --> 14:01.382
You must be that…
By any chance, how old…

14:03.342 --> 14:05.594
Ah… Never mind.

14:05.678 --> 14:07.930
What? Tell me! Who is he talking about?

14:08.889 --> 14:10.266
-No clue.
-That older girl.

14:10.349 --> 14:12.226
-[whispers] Just drink.
-[clears throat]

14:12.309 --> 14:15.354
Geez, how did that older girl
end up being forgotten like that?

14:16.605 --> 14:18.148
Hey, Yeon Tae-seo.

14:18.899 --> 14:22.486
-We only dated briefly.
-She was crazy about him. I even cried.

14:22.570 --> 14:24.238
[groans] Now, I'm curious.

14:24.321 --> 14:25.614
What did she do?

14:27.157 --> 14:30.911
Mmm… She was very pure.

14:30.995 --> 14:32.162
Stop making things up.

14:32.246 --> 14:34.832
She was purely persistent.
[inhales sharply]

14:34.915 --> 14:37.918
-And also, when was that again?
-"Also"?

14:38.002 --> 14:39.670
-Perhaps…
-Nothing.

14:39.753 --> 14:41.964
Right, there's nothing in my glass.

14:42.047 --> 14:43.173
Mmm…

14:44.633 --> 14:46.427
[Tae-seo]
It looks like you can really drink.

14:47.595 --> 14:48.721
Only take a glass or two.

14:49.346 --> 14:50.639
I can't drink more than that.

14:51.891 --> 14:53.893
I'd only drink just one glass
with the guests too.

14:53.976 --> 14:54.810
Guests?

14:54.894 --> 14:57.521
[chuckles softly]
I used to run a guesthouse.

14:58.230 --> 15:00.149
I poured my heart and soul into it,

15:00.774 --> 15:02.109
but I got blindsided.

15:02.610 --> 15:03.819
They took everything.

15:04.820 --> 15:06.780
[Hyeong-seok]
Man, that must've been hard. Cheers!

15:07.364 --> 15:11.160
-I got way too serious. I'll stop here.
-[Hyeong-seok] Yeah, we only just met.

15:11.243 --> 15:14.079
-I was a little thrown off.
-[Eun-a chuckles] Sorry.

15:15.080 --> 15:17.207
A lot of girls liked Tae-seo
in high school, right?

15:17.291 --> 15:19.919
-Nope. We went to an all-boys school.
-Yeah, it was all boys.

15:20.002 --> 15:21.045
What?

15:21.128 --> 15:24.506
But when he first transferred,
his bag was full of girls' name tags.

15:24.590 --> 15:26.008
What? It was only one or two.

15:26.091 --> 15:28.594
Ah, it must be from the study center.

15:29.178 --> 15:31.472
[smacks lips]
You did something behind my back!

15:32.097 --> 15:33.849
Hey, who did you get name tags from?

15:33.933 --> 15:37.519
-I told you it's rude to point like that.
-Who was it?

15:40.147 --> 15:41.231
Hey.

15:41.315 --> 15:43.567
I saw that. [loudly] Ma'am!

15:43.651 --> 15:45.069
You don't allow takeout here.

15:45.152 --> 15:47.237
Why does A-sol's family
always get special treatment?

15:47.321 --> 15:49.073
-[woman] Just let it go.
-[Hyeong-seok tuts]

15:49.156 --> 15:51.158
[quirky music plays]

16:00.167 --> 16:02.169
[music ends]

16:04.797 --> 16:05.965
[Eun-a] Wow.

16:09.551 --> 16:12.429
[Tae-seo] Are you okay?
You were drinking a lot.

16:13.055 --> 16:15.975
[Eun-a] Yeah, I'm pleasantly tipsy.

16:18.227 --> 16:20.312
So you were here
before you came to Yeonwoo.

16:24.400 --> 16:25.234
Earlier…

16:28.237 --> 16:29.947
what did you mean by "blindsided"?

16:31.532 --> 16:33.450
[Eun-a]
I was living in the residence hall,

16:33.534 --> 16:37.246
and then I thought I'd try living
in a proper house for once.

16:38.747 --> 16:42.292
But I didn't rewrite the contract
when I turned it into a guesthouse.

16:42.835 --> 16:44.253
They said it was fine.

16:45.838 --> 16:49.008
[sniffles] But when I started doing well,
they kicked me out.

16:51.635 --> 16:53.804
Then, I came to Seoul

16:54.847 --> 16:56.640
and met Yeon Tae-seo.

17:00.394 --> 17:01.478
[chuckles softly]

17:03.272 --> 17:05.566
How long did you go out
with that older girl?

17:06.567 --> 17:07.901
[Tae-seo sighs]

17:09.153 --> 17:10.112
A year.

17:13.615 --> 17:15.909
A year is quite a long while
for Yeon Tae-seo.

17:16.493 --> 17:18.037
That's how long I've known her for.

17:18.787 --> 17:21.040
I dated her for… [inhales sharply]

17:21.123 --> 17:22.708
…less than a month, I think.

17:23.542 --> 17:24.460
You?

17:26.045 --> 17:28.422
That person you're ending things with.

17:28.505 --> 17:30.174
How long did you two date?

17:32.426 --> 17:33.594
About three months.

17:34.386 --> 17:35.804
I've known him for longer.

17:42.311 --> 17:43.771
Your profile hasn't changed.

17:45.689 --> 17:46.648
[chuckles]

17:47.149 --> 17:49.234
We usually sat next to each other.

17:50.277 --> 17:53.572
In the library and on bus trips.

17:54.823 --> 17:57.993
It's strange, but when I think of you,
I think of your profile.

18:01.830 --> 18:03.082
But something's different.

18:04.124 --> 18:05.793
Maybe it's the air around you?

18:07.294 --> 18:08.587
You're exactly the same.

18:08.670 --> 18:10.506
I looked like this when I was 20?

18:10.589 --> 18:12.549
[exclaims] No way.

18:13.175 --> 18:15.552
Uh, there's something that's different.

18:16.220 --> 18:17.054
You…

18:17.763 --> 18:20.432
do these gestures when you're talking now.

18:20.516 --> 18:23.102
-[Eun-a chuckles]
-What is this?

18:23.769 --> 18:25.521
Did I not do that before?

18:26.271 --> 18:27.231
You too, actually.

18:27.314 --> 18:29.942
It was when you casually said earlier,

18:30.025 --> 18:31.151
"A year."

18:32.444 --> 18:34.196
That didn't feel like you.

18:36.490 --> 18:39.201
But then again, maybe it is like you.

18:41.161 --> 18:42.663
You and I both…

18:42.746 --> 18:45.249
[breathes heavily] Well,

18:45.332 --> 18:48.418
it's our first time seeing someone
we broke up with after ten years.

18:52.172 --> 18:53.257
[Tae-seo sighs]

18:58.262 --> 18:59.888
We didn't break up.

19:04.059 --> 19:05.227
It didn't happen in person.

19:05.894 --> 19:07.980
How can we break up
without even seeing each other?

19:08.063 --> 19:10.065
-Hey…
-That's what I kept telling myself.

19:12.109 --> 19:13.819
Then, I eventually accepted it.

19:15.237 --> 19:16.905
"We didn't break up."

19:17.573 --> 19:19.449
"I can't break up with Tae-seo like this."

19:22.411 --> 19:24.913
We ended things in July, so…

19:27.958 --> 19:28.792
Mmm…

19:30.460 --> 19:32.171
I told myself that for six months.

19:33.172 --> 19:34.006
Then…

19:35.924 --> 19:36.925
Then?

19:38.552 --> 19:40.345
Then, I stopped convincing myself.

19:42.306 --> 19:44.766
What about you?
You didn't think of it that way at all?

19:46.059 --> 19:48.687
When it's over, it's over. [inhales]

19:49.396 --> 19:51.190
I didn't think… [sighs]

19:51.273 --> 19:53.734
…there would be anything more.

19:57.196 --> 19:58.322
It's over.

19:59.281 --> 20:01.283
What we had then is over.

20:02.117 --> 20:03.327
Now…

20:04.620 --> 20:05.829
we're different,

20:06.914 --> 20:07.831
but also the same…

20:09.625 --> 20:10.751
No.

20:11.919 --> 20:12.753
Never mind.

20:15.589 --> 20:16.423
Mmm…

20:19.593 --> 20:21.094
I'm surprised by that too.

20:22.221 --> 20:24.640
[gentle music playing]

20:24.723 --> 20:25.891
[exhales]

20:26.683 --> 20:27.935
It's the same.

20:29.269 --> 20:30.938
My feelings are the same.

20:33.023 --> 20:35.234
You're someone I liked ten years ago,

20:37.027 --> 20:38.570
but I still feel the same way.

20:40.864 --> 20:43.116
I didn't know that would be possible,

20:45.911 --> 20:47.246
but it's been seamless.

20:49.623 --> 20:50.457
Me too.

20:52.876 --> 20:55.254
It was like that the moment I saw you.

21:03.053 --> 21:05.389
I guess no one can defeat
Mo Eun-a from ten years ago…

21:05.472 --> 21:08.100
[sniffles, sighs deeply]

21:09.059 --> 21:10.978
…except Mo Eun-a herself.

21:14.606 --> 21:16.900
[sighs] That's really nice.

21:18.193 --> 21:19.945
It feels like
everything's been made up for.

21:21.989 --> 21:23.031
Then…

21:27.160 --> 21:28.912
we're back together again?

21:41.008 --> 21:42.592
Thanks, Tae-seo.

21:44.261 --> 21:46.263
[music fades]

21:46.346 --> 21:49.016
[Hyeong-seok groans]
Why would they fight in a study café?

21:49.099 --> 21:51.268
Geez, kids are scary these days.

21:51.351 --> 21:52.936
-[Tae-seo groans]
-[Hyeong-seok grunts]

21:53.979 --> 21:56.440
[hesitates] You can sit down.
It's okay to ignore him.

21:56.523 --> 21:57.482
[Eun-a] Okay.

22:03.572 --> 22:05.782
She's that girl from ten years ago, right?

22:07.409 --> 22:12.706
[sighs] I pretended not to know on purpose
and even talked about that older girl.

22:12.789 --> 22:16.251
I made it sound like
you did just fine without her. [chuckles]

22:17.502 --> 22:19.421
-[sighs in relief]
-Give me one too.

22:20.005 --> 22:22.090
-You don't smoke.
-Just give me one.

22:23.925 --> 22:24.926
[clicks tongue]

22:25.719 --> 22:26.720
[Hyeong-seok grunts]

22:34.770 --> 22:36.772
[emotional music playing]

23:28.824 --> 23:30.826
[music ends]

23:32.702 --> 23:34.996
-[Eun-a] Did you sleep well?
-[guest] Yes, we did.

23:35.080 --> 23:39.334
Ah, I thought this might help you find
some nice places to visit around here.

23:39.417 --> 23:41.294
Yes, thank you. We'll take a look.

23:41.378 --> 23:42.337
[cellphone vibrates]

23:47.676 --> 23:50.512
[Seong-chan] <i>Tell me what needs to stay</i>
<i>or be thrown away.</i>

23:50.595 --> 23:52.722
<i>-I'm cleaning out the back house.</i>
-[sighs]

24:03.275 --> 24:04.442
[cellphone vibrates]

24:08.780 --> 24:10.407
[Eun-a] <i>You don't need to clean it out.</i>

24:10.490 --> 24:11.950
-[somber music playing]
-[sighs]

24:12.617 --> 24:14.703
[Seong-chan]
<i>You want me to leave your things to rot?</i>

24:14.786 --> 24:16.872
<i>-Tell me what you'll keep.</i>
<i>-</i>[indistinct conversation]

24:16.955 --> 24:20.167
[Eun-a] <i>Send all the clothes and bedding</i>
<i>to the community center.</i>

24:20.250 --> 24:21.751
<i>They'll sort it out themselves.</i>

24:22.460 --> 24:24.171
<i>Just send the items</i>
<i>I've listed to Yeonwoo.</i>

24:24.754 --> 24:26.631
[Seong-chan]
<i>You're not even going to Yeonwoo.</i>

24:26.715 --> 24:28.967
<i>Send me your address in Seoul</i>
<i>that I can send these to.</i>

24:29.676 --> 24:30.719
[cellphone vibrates]

24:35.682 --> 24:37.726
[Tae-seo]
<i>I'll come see you after I finish work.</i>

24:37.809 --> 24:40.312
<i>Tell me your nearest station.</i>
<i>I'll go only as far as there.</i>

24:55.452 --> 24:56.661
[man] Hello.

24:57.162 --> 24:59.873
[chuckles softly]
I'm Train Operator Choi Su-cheol.

24:59.956 --> 25:02.792
-I took photos of Oido Station. [chuckles]
-[chuckling] Right.

25:02.876 --> 25:04.211
-Hello.
-Hello.

25:04.294 --> 25:06.129
I believe we've only spoken over texts

25:06.213 --> 25:08.798
since train operators
rarely get to see each other.

25:08.882 --> 25:11.301
Did you hear
about the frame size and wood type?

25:11.384 --> 25:13.470
I did, but actually…

25:14.221 --> 25:16.181
I'd like to change the photo.

25:16.264 --> 25:18.683
[hesitates] Could you take a look?

25:18.767 --> 25:19.976
-Do you have it with you?
-Yes.

25:20.685 --> 25:23.855
[Su-cheol] Some had been taken before,
and a few were retaken.

25:24.606 --> 25:26.775
-They're really good.
-[chuckles] Thank you.

25:26.858 --> 25:27.734
[cellphone vibrates]

25:27.817 --> 25:29.986
-Sorry, one second.
-Sure.

25:32.322 --> 25:34.658
[Eun-a]<i> I have to stay here this evening.</i>

25:34.741 --> 25:37.410
<i>I'm meeting my boss for the first time</i>
<i>since coming to Seoul.</i>

25:37.494 --> 25:40.288
<i>I think he has something to say to me.</i>
<i>Let's meet another day.</i>

25:41.790 --> 25:43.083
Those flowers…

25:44.042 --> 25:45.293
Don't put them in the rooms.

25:45.377 --> 25:47.337
If we stop doing that later,
people will complain.

25:47.921 --> 25:48.838
And in the break room,

25:48.922 --> 25:51.216
do not use the gas
under any circumstances.

25:52.592 --> 25:55.553
There was a manager
who once secretly ate and slept there,

25:55.637 --> 25:57.305
and then a fire broke out one night.

25:57.389 --> 25:58.223
Okay.

25:59.432 --> 26:00.892
What about the laundry service?

26:01.518 --> 26:03.436
[Eun-a's boss] I'm trying to find one.

26:03.520 --> 26:05.689
But maybe I'll make a laundry room.
What do you think?

26:06.564 --> 26:09.359
A professional service is much better.
They use different equipment.

26:09.442 --> 26:11.486
Washing machines
are really good these days.

26:14.114 --> 26:16.658
By the way, when Hae-jin
handed over duties to you,

26:17.492 --> 26:20.203
she didn't mention that we don't have
reservations from next week.

26:20.287 --> 26:21.746
It's being rented out for two weeks.

26:22.289 --> 26:24.457
They'll be filming here,
so it won't be busy.

26:24.541 --> 26:26.293
You can just stay here
until you clock out.

26:28.420 --> 26:30.422
[somber music playing]

26:45.770 --> 26:46.646
SEONG-CHAN

26:46.730 --> 26:49.232
YOU'RE NOT EVEN GOING TO YEONWOO

26:49.316 --> 26:52.777
SEND ME YOUR ADDRESS IN SEOUL
THAT I CAN SEND THESE TO

26:54.988 --> 26:57.115
[Eun-a]<i> Just leave my things to rot</i>
<i>in the back house.</i>

27:05.373 --> 27:07.375
[music fades]

27:08.626 --> 27:09.836
[Tae-seo] Someone's exhausted.

27:17.927 --> 27:18.762
Eun-a.

27:20.638 --> 27:21.931
[Eun-a] No, I just…

27:22.640 --> 27:23.808
Sorry.

27:24.392 --> 27:25.602
It's just that…

27:26.436 --> 27:27.395
Somehow,

27:28.521 --> 27:30.857
when I was feeling exhausted after work,

27:31.858 --> 27:34.235
you're standing here right in front of me.

27:35.153 --> 27:36.988
The very person I wanted to see.

27:38.281 --> 27:39.115
How?

27:39.199 --> 27:40.992
You should've said you wanted to see me.

27:42.952 --> 27:44.913
[gentle music playing]

27:45.538 --> 27:46.664
Well…

27:46.748 --> 27:49.584
It's not that hard.
I can be here in no time.

27:51.252 --> 27:52.087
[chuckles softly]

27:57.884 --> 27:59.177
You made it through well today

28:00.470 --> 28:01.471
in this tough city.

28:16.027 --> 28:18.363
[Eun-a] I need Yeon Tae-seo's broad back.

28:20.156 --> 28:21.741
Not my arms but my back?

28:27.163 --> 28:28.581
[Eun-a] I need your back for today.

28:31.584 --> 28:33.002
This feels nice.

28:48.351 --> 28:50.353
[music fades]

29:01.114 --> 29:02.240
[cellphone vibrates]

29:03.992 --> 29:07.662
[Eun-a]<i> Let's meet at my workplace today.</i>
<i>I'll send you the address.</i>

29:12.917 --> 29:14.169
[cellphone vibrates]

29:19.799 --> 29:21.468
[Tae-seo] <i>You're really good at your job.</i>

29:26.139 --> 29:27.348
[chuckles softly]

29:30.894 --> 29:32.437
[cellphone vibrates]

29:34.147 --> 29:35.523
What is it?

29:35.607 --> 29:37.484
The lamp's broken, so I'm checking it.

29:37.567 --> 29:39.486
-Just wait one second.
-Okay.

29:47.452 --> 29:49.454
[soft romantic music builds]

29:59.506 --> 30:01.716
[soft romantic music playing]

30:16.898 --> 30:18.650
-[Eun-a exclaims]
-[plastic wrapper rustles]

30:18.733 --> 30:19.943
[Tae-seo exclaims] Nice.

30:21.694 --> 30:23.696
[music continues playing]

30:25.990 --> 30:27.367
Thanks for the ice cream.

30:28.785 --> 30:29.828
Hey.

30:33.373 --> 30:34.749
[bell rings]

30:55.812 --> 30:58.356
[grunts, groans]

30:59.524 --> 31:00.650
I need some coffee.

31:13.496 --> 31:14.831
[music fades]

31:14.914 --> 31:15.748
Say "Ah."

31:17.000 --> 31:19.168
Eat this. They say it helps you wake up.

31:21.337 --> 31:22.338
[exhales]

31:23.256 --> 31:26.259
-Thanks. You're helping me focus.
-[Eun-a chuckles]

31:31.264 --> 31:32.098
Mmm…

31:33.016 --> 31:34.642
Why does he want to change the photo?

31:34.726 --> 31:36.477
[inhales sharply] Well…

31:37.145 --> 31:38.897
Now that the exhibition
is really happening,

31:39.397 --> 31:40.398
I guess he's unsure.

31:41.065 --> 31:42.358
He even brought his old photos.

31:43.818 --> 31:45.236
But I like that one.

31:47.614 --> 31:48.448
[Tae-seo] Me too.

31:49.324 --> 31:50.909
He said he'll think about it some more.

31:52.911 --> 31:55.079
Is there anything I can do?
I want to help.

31:57.123 --> 31:58.666
[both] Mmm…

31:58.750 --> 31:59.959
Should I clean up?

32:00.043 --> 32:01.210
[chuckles] No, it's okay.

32:03.671 --> 32:05.924
Put these photos on the board for me.

32:06.966 --> 32:08.760
-Any way I want to?
-Sure.

32:38.206 --> 32:39.707
Are these scraps? Can I use them?

32:40.750 --> 32:41.793
Sure.

32:55.515 --> 32:57.100
Are you going to keep living in Seoul?

32:59.352 --> 33:00.353
Hmm…

33:01.145 --> 33:02.522
That might be difficult.

33:02.605 --> 33:04.732
Hui-seo's just bought me some time.

33:05.400 --> 33:08.111
When my grandparents become
too much for him, I need to move back.

33:11.531 --> 33:13.950
Was that your plan from the start?

33:15.368 --> 33:16.202
[Tae-seo] Yeah.

33:17.203 --> 33:19.330
[smacks lips] Just for a brief while,

33:20.081 --> 33:23.209
I thought I could put myself first.

33:26.170 --> 33:27.755
My life here

33:29.257 --> 33:30.425
has an expiration date.

33:31.884 --> 33:33.636
Hui-seo might be able to handle it.

33:34.679 --> 33:35.638
It'll be hard.

33:37.432 --> 33:39.726
He still can't travel outside Yeonwoo.

33:40.351 --> 33:42.979
He's made a life for himself in that town,

33:43.688 --> 33:44.856
and I'm proud of him.

33:44.939 --> 33:46.315
[breathes heavily]

33:46.399 --> 33:47.859
I can't wish for more.

33:57.577 --> 33:58.786
Until when?

34:05.126 --> 34:06.419
Why aren't you answering?

34:11.591 --> 34:14.260
You asked, so I thought about it.

34:14.343 --> 34:15.178
But…

34:16.304 --> 34:18.890
I don't really know if that's up to me.

34:19.557 --> 34:22.810
It could be sooner than expected
or much later.

34:24.896 --> 34:27.106
[tuts] I'll think about it
when I get there.

34:28.483 --> 34:31.194
Will you be able to settle things quickly
when the time comes?

34:32.612 --> 34:33.654
I have to.

34:38.785 --> 34:40.411
[Eun-a] I hope it goes the way you want.

34:44.373 --> 34:45.416
Do you…

34:46.501 --> 34:48.127
see yourself getting married?

34:53.466 --> 34:54.300
[Tae-seo] Yeah.

34:56.636 --> 34:58.763
[slow instrumental music playing]

34:58.846 --> 34:59.680
What about you?

35:01.891 --> 35:04.477
I've never even dared to think about it.

35:06.229 --> 35:09.232
You're going to live
in either Seoul or Yeonwoo, right?

35:12.151 --> 35:13.277
I'll have to see.

35:14.028 --> 35:15.988
[Eun-a] Deciding where to live

35:16.072 --> 35:17.657
isn't as easy as it seems.

35:19.158 --> 35:22.662
Still, wherever it is,
I feel comfortable when I'm with you.

35:24.872 --> 35:28.000
When you're traveling,
that place feels like reality,

35:28.709 --> 35:30.211
and your actual home feels distant.

35:30.878 --> 35:32.380
But when you come back,

35:32.463 --> 35:34.549
your home feels real,

35:34.632 --> 35:35.967
and where you were feels distant,

35:36.926 --> 35:38.136
as if it was fake.

35:41.097 --> 35:43.391
It felt unreal being in Seoul.

35:44.142 --> 35:46.269
I ended up coming here out of nowhere.

35:47.854 --> 35:48.688
[exclaims]

35:49.188 --> 35:50.940
I told myself this wasn't real

35:51.649 --> 35:53.317
and I was trapped inside a lie.

35:54.193 --> 35:57.655
But when I look at you,
this place feels real.

35:59.991 --> 36:01.450
I think, "That's right."

36:01.534 --> 36:02.535
"It was here."

36:05.663 --> 36:06.664
You were here,

36:06.747 --> 36:08.249
so it became real.

36:10.126 --> 36:11.836
You said the same thing back then.

36:11.919 --> 36:14.255
Oh, you remember that?

36:15.715 --> 36:17.091
So…

36:21.554 --> 36:22.555
stay right by my side.

36:23.806 --> 36:25.391
Okay, I will.

36:28.227 --> 36:29.228
Mmm…

36:30.354 --> 36:32.148
When was your loneliest birthday?

36:32.231 --> 36:34.650
[laughs] Where did that come from?

36:36.068 --> 36:38.154
Mmm, we've never celebrated our birthdays.

36:38.237 --> 36:41.616
Mine's July 28th,
the day before you transferred.

36:41.699 --> 36:43.367
Yours is November 9th.

36:44.118 --> 36:46.370
But you never told me,
so we just spent it studying.

36:46.871 --> 36:50.374
Tell me. I just need to write the date.
When was your loneliest birthday?

36:53.753 --> 36:55.671
It was in 2016 when I was in the army.

37:00.593 --> 37:02.178
Besides 2016.

37:03.888 --> 37:06.057
Last year? I'll pick last year.

37:07.391 --> 37:08.726
Were you lonely last year?

37:09.268 --> 37:11.729
[chuckling] You told me
to think about it, so I did just that.

37:11.812 --> 37:13.147
It doesn't mean anything.

37:25.493 --> 37:26.577
[Eun-a] Ta-da!

37:27.536 --> 37:29.747
Congratulations on the last birthday
of your twenties.

37:29.830 --> 37:32.083
-[Tae-seo chuckles]
-[Eun-a giggling]

37:33.751 --> 37:36.921
HAPPY BIRTHDAY
NOVEMBER 9, 2024

37:37.004 --> 37:39.006
[pleasant music playing]

37:45.304 --> 37:46.347
And my present?

37:46.430 --> 37:48.599
Mmm? Your present?

37:48.683 --> 37:51.769
[inhales sharply] Mmm, your present…

37:58.901 --> 37:59.735
Happy birthday.

38:03.364 --> 38:04.490
Happy?

38:05.574 --> 38:07.451
[both giggling]

38:11.330 --> 38:12.832
[cellphone vibrating]

38:13.582 --> 38:15.418
Oh, Hui-seo's calling.

38:16.002 --> 38:17.253
It must be urgent.

38:17.878 --> 38:18.838
You should pick up.

38:19.338 --> 38:20.256
[whispers] One second.

38:21.882 --> 38:22.717
Hey, Hui-seo.

38:22.800 --> 38:24.969
You know Grandma's going
to the hospital next week?

38:25.553 --> 38:27.430
I know. She's getting a checkup.

38:28.639 --> 38:31.600
[Hui-seo] <i>I'm going to take her,</i>
<i>so I just called to tell you not to worry.</i>

38:33.102 --> 38:34.562
<i>Weren't you worried?</i>

38:34.645 --> 38:37.815
Why would I be? You'll do just fine.

38:37.898 --> 38:40.276
[Hui-seo]
<i>Anyway, just give Grandma a call.</i>

38:40.359 --> 38:43.029
Do I really have to remind you
to call her though?

38:43.112 --> 38:44.572
<i>You could at least say,</i>

38:44.655 --> 38:47.992
<i>"I should be there, but I can't go.</i>
<i>Man, I feel terrible."</i>

38:48.075 --> 38:49.660
<i>Is that so hard? Huh?</i>

38:49.744 --> 38:52.413
<i>-Don't you even feel sorry for me?</i>
-Thank you,

38:53.289 --> 38:54.123
Hui-seo.

38:55.207 --> 38:56.959
[Hui-seo sighs, tuts] <i>Sure.</i>

38:57.585 --> 38:59.128
<i>Don't forget to call Grandma.</i>

38:59.211 --> 39:00.796
I'll call first thing in the morning.

39:01.881 --> 39:02.715
Okay, bye.

39:05.176 --> 39:06.010
[line disconnects]

39:07.553 --> 39:08.637
[thuds]

39:09.180 --> 39:10.014
Hmm?

39:10.681 --> 39:12.183
Hmm? [chuckles]

39:14.310 --> 39:16.312
[slow romantic music playing]

39:18.856 --> 39:21.400
[Tae-seo breathes deeply, grunts]

39:30.493 --> 39:33.496
This is for 2023.

39:34.080 --> 39:37.249
[laughing]

39:40.795 --> 39:44.340
This is for 2022.

39:51.889 --> 39:54.392
[whispers] This is for 2021.

39:54.475 --> 39:56.477
[music swells]

40:18.958 --> 40:20.960
[music ends]

40:21.043 --> 40:22.169
[exclaims]

40:23.129 --> 40:25.631
Ah, this <i>godeulppaegi</i> kimchi is amazing.

40:27.967 --> 40:29.176
Have it with some soup.

40:30.052 --> 40:32.012
I made a lot of kimchi.

40:32.763 --> 40:36.225
Who knows what might happen
when I visit the hospital next week?

40:36.308 --> 40:39.437
You're just going in for a checkup
and coming straight home.

40:40.479 --> 40:44.775
Tae-seo likes kimchi,
but there's no way to get it to him.

40:53.993 --> 40:55.911
[rope zips]

40:56.537 --> 40:58.789
-[Jin-su grunts]
-Why is there so much?

40:58.873 --> 41:01.917
[sighs] It's a year's worth.
Some of it's for other clients too.

41:02.001 --> 41:03.544
[hesitates] Will Tae-seo be home?

41:03.627 --> 41:06.839
Of course not.
I can't fit into his schedule.

41:07.631 --> 41:10.301
I can just leave these inside.
It seems he got more jobs.

41:10.384 --> 41:12.219
-Jobs?
-[Jin-su] Yeah.

41:13.387 --> 41:15.055
What on earth is he up to?

41:16.640 --> 41:17.641
I'm coming with you.

41:18.392 --> 41:21.228
I'll be coming back late at night
after I visit all my clients.

41:21.312 --> 41:23.856
That's fine by me. [inhales sharply]

41:23.939 --> 41:25.983
My brother will be shocked to see me.

41:26.066 --> 41:28.152
Are you sure you can go?
What about the post office?

41:28.903 --> 41:30.446
I worked the morning shift today.

41:31.489 --> 41:35.034
-Are you here to pick up the wood? Mmm…
-[Hui-seo whispers] Don't tell my grandma.

41:35.117 --> 41:36.202
I'll say I'm going to work.

41:36.911 --> 41:38.162
[in normal voice] Grandma.

41:38.245 --> 41:40.372
Jin-su said he can bring
the kimchi to Tae-seo.

41:40.456 --> 41:41.415
Could you pack some up?

41:41.499 --> 41:43.334
[Hwa-sun chuckling] Goodness.

41:43.417 --> 41:46.128
Thank you so much.
I'll go pack it up right now, okay?

41:46.212 --> 41:47.338
[Jin-su] Sure.

42:16.242 --> 42:17.493
[Eun-a] "Amy Park."

42:29.964 --> 42:31.549
[door opens, closes]

42:53.779 --> 42:54.613
[So-hyeon chuckles]

42:56.532 --> 42:57.366
Amy Park.

42:58.242 --> 42:59.827
I came to see you.

43:04.707 --> 43:05.833
[grunts]

43:07.918 --> 43:09.253
[exclaims]

43:09.920 --> 43:11.171
This is nice.

43:11.255 --> 43:13.757
[chuckles] I can't believe how nice it is.

43:15.050 --> 43:16.343
Have a pleasant stay.

43:21.765 --> 43:23.100
[smacks lips] Eun-a.

43:24.268 --> 43:25.352
[loudly] Mo Eun-a!

43:30.816 --> 43:32.401
Here, give it to me.

43:35.571 --> 43:37.615
[Hui-seo panting]

43:38.574 --> 43:41.160
Geez, I knew he'd be living like this.

43:41.744 --> 43:43.329
Cup noodles and rice snacks.

43:44.288 --> 43:46.498
-Honestly. [exhales]
-[Jin-su sighs]

43:49.918 --> 43:52.129
You're beaming
now that you're at your brother's.

43:52.838 --> 43:53.964
He'll be happy to see you.

43:54.048 --> 43:55.215
[laughs]

43:55.716 --> 43:57.551
-You should go do your rounds.
-[Jin-su] Okay.

43:57.635 --> 44:00.304
I'll call you on my way here.
I'll come as soon as possible.

44:01.096 --> 44:02.222
Don't worry about me.

44:02.306 --> 44:04.892
This is my brother's place.
I can sleep over if I have to.

44:04.975 --> 44:05.976
[chuckles]

44:09.355 --> 44:11.440
-See you.
-[Jin-su] Bye.

44:12.232 --> 44:13.150
[door closes]

44:14.109 --> 44:16.111
Geez, look at all that laundry
lying around.

44:17.488 --> 44:18.656
One, two.

44:20.783 --> 44:23.661
He still wears his gym shorts?
Are they his favorite or something?

44:38.926 --> 44:40.678
[doorbell rings]

44:42.346 --> 44:43.472
[sighs in frustration]

44:44.264 --> 44:46.058
Of course, he's not here.

44:50.688 --> 44:53.232
<i>I sent the painting by courier.</i>

44:53.315 --> 44:56.443
<i>He complained there was no elevator.</i>

44:56.527 --> 44:57.945
<i>-He left it in front of…</i>
-Excuse me?

44:58.028 --> 44:59.363
[A-sol screams]

45:05.619 --> 45:06.578
Granny.

45:07.162 --> 45:10.249
It looks like Mo Eun-a's house
got international mail again.

45:10.958 --> 45:12.584
It's from Hawaii this time.

45:13.961 --> 45:15.129
Granny?

45:18.173 --> 45:19.049
[panicking] Granny!

45:31.311 --> 45:32.729
You're Mr. Yeon Tae-seo's brother?

45:33.730 --> 45:35.357
Yes, why do you ask?

45:35.441 --> 45:36.275
Uh…

45:36.942 --> 45:38.694
I told him I'd send it by courier,

45:38.777 --> 45:40.737
but I had time so I came in person.

45:41.447 --> 45:43.824
-You can just leave it here.
-[A-sol] Okay.

45:44.616 --> 45:46.118
I'll leave it with you.

45:49.037 --> 45:51.248
[cellphone vibrating]

45:52.875 --> 45:55.377
Hi, Hyang-gi. What is it?

45:57.463 --> 45:59.465
[somber music playing]

45:59.965 --> 46:01.258
[loud thud]

46:06.305 --> 46:07.556
Could you help me up?

46:08.557 --> 46:09.766
[hesitates] Right, sure.

46:10.392 --> 46:12.394
[train railings squeaking]

46:15.856 --> 46:17.566
[hydraulics hissing]

46:22.696 --> 46:24.865
3 MISSED CALLS

46:24.948 --> 46:26.241
OLD HOUSE IM A-SOL

46:26.325 --> 46:28.327
[line ringing]

46:31.663 --> 46:33.540
-[A-sol] <i>I can't get into it right now.</i>
-Sorry?

46:33.624 --> 46:35.584
<i>Your grandmother collapsed.</i>

46:35.667 --> 46:37.586
<i>I met your brother at your house.</i>

46:37.669 --> 46:40.214
<i>We're on our way to the hospital,</i>
<i>so please come right away.</i>

46:41.131 --> 46:42.424
I'll explain everything later.

46:42.508 --> 46:44.259
I was told you know which hospital it is.

46:44.343 --> 46:46.053
[Tae-seo] <i>Please put Hui-seo on the phone.</i>

46:46.136 --> 46:48.138
[dramatic music playing]

46:49.890 --> 46:51.517
He's asleep. I think it was the nerves.

46:52.184 --> 46:54.144
He's allowed to visit his brother, right?

46:56.104 --> 46:58.524
<i>As for me, I was going to send</i>
<i>the painting by courier, but--</i>

46:58.607 --> 47:00.108
Hui-seo.

47:00.192 --> 47:01.527
<i>You can hear me, right?</i>

47:01.610 --> 47:04.321
I just finished my work,
so I can come right away.

47:05.030 --> 47:07.699
Don't get anxious
and massage your leg on the way.

47:08.450 --> 47:09.952
<i>Don't be nervous. Keep breathing.</i>

47:11.286 --> 47:12.204
<i>It's okay.</i>

47:13.497 --> 47:14.456
Okay, Tae-seo.

47:15.082 --> 47:17.084
[music swells]

47:22.214 --> 47:25.801
Hello? I don't think
I can make tomorrow's shift.

47:26.468 --> 47:28.554
Yes. Okay, thank you.

47:30.347 --> 47:32.349
[music fades]

47:34.434 --> 47:36.520
Let's get some bean sprout and rice soup.

47:36.603 --> 47:39.356
I'm feeling a bit sick
after all that wine on the plane.

47:39.439 --> 47:40.524
I need to cure my hangover.

47:42.109 --> 47:43.902
I'll have one delivered here, ma'am.

47:43.986 --> 47:47.030
[loudly] Let's go to a restaurant and eat!

47:50.742 --> 47:51.577
[slurps]

47:52.953 --> 47:54.871
[sighs in relief] That hits the spot.
[chuckles]

47:55.914 --> 47:57.374
I feel so much better now.

47:59.084 --> 47:59.918
[slurps]

48:00.669 --> 48:03.005
It's a good thing
you broke up with Seong-chan.

48:03.088 --> 48:06.466
He has to have you all to himself
and make you work with only him,

48:06.550 --> 48:07.551
so you end up all alone.

48:08.135 --> 48:09.928
-So you still talk to him.
-[So-hyeon slurps]

48:10.012 --> 48:11.179
But he's not a bad person.

48:12.014 --> 48:13.265
He's paying for the lawsuit.

48:14.474 --> 48:16.476
He doesn't even have that kind of money.

48:16.560 --> 48:18.812
He's going to spend
his entire life savings on that suit.

48:19.563 --> 48:21.398
That's not going to solve anything.

48:24.651 --> 48:25.694
I'm not done yet.

48:26.320 --> 48:27.696
Don't stay at Na-yeong's either.

48:27.779 --> 48:30.198
Why are you wandering around
as if you don't have a home?

48:30.282 --> 48:32.075
When Na-yeong told me where you worked,

48:32.159 --> 48:33.952
she acted like
she was doing me a huge favor.

48:34.036 --> 48:37.539
There's only one person
who knows where I am and told Na-yeong.

48:38.832 --> 48:39.958
Now, to the main point.

48:41.335 --> 48:42.586
The guesthouse you used to run.

48:43.295 --> 48:44.338
You need to go back to it.

48:48.425 --> 48:52.054
Seong-chan's bent on a lawsuit
I didn't even ask for, and now you.

48:52.721 --> 48:55.098
What's with you two? What is your deal?

48:55.182 --> 48:56.892
I don't know what he's thinking.

48:57.809 --> 48:59.478
I came to settle your situation.

49:00.646 --> 49:01.897
That guesthouse you ran.

49:01.980 --> 49:04.149
Seong-chan only found out
about it through me.

49:05.275 --> 49:06.109
[So-hyeon slurps]

49:08.612 --> 49:10.447
How else would he have known?

49:11.323 --> 49:14.701
I knew about it because
I was going around looking into things.

49:16.995 --> 49:20.415
I'm saying the property owner
is someone I know.

49:21.583 --> 49:22.876
I'm going to settle this.

49:24.252 --> 49:27.714
You just take back what's yours
and go back to living your life.

49:29.966 --> 49:31.426
You're at it again.

49:32.010 --> 49:33.553
Are you that desperate to play my mom?

49:33.637 --> 49:36.390
You should be good to your own mother
and stop causing her grief.

49:36.973 --> 49:37.808
[laughs]

49:40.143 --> 49:42.104
I'm here because my mom made such a fuss.

49:43.188 --> 49:45.649
She prays for you at dawn every day.

49:45.732 --> 49:48.276
She barely knows you,
and yet she prefers you over me.

49:54.616 --> 49:57.744
You have the right to stay there
until your lease is up,

49:57.828 --> 49:58.787
so run your guesthouse.

49:59.746 --> 50:01.456
After that, I can't stop them.

50:02.124 --> 50:03.125
Then…

50:07.462 --> 50:08.630
go back to Yeonwoo.

50:10.632 --> 50:11.675
It's your home.

50:14.469 --> 50:17.431
-If you don't like Yeonwoo…
-You go to Yeonwoo.

50:18.890 --> 50:20.267
It's been empty for ten years.

50:22.811 --> 50:23.770
[chuckles dryly]

50:25.355 --> 50:26.356
[in English] Okay.

50:27.607 --> 50:29.526
[in Korean]
Anything else you want me to do?

50:30.110 --> 50:31.778
Anything while I'm there?

50:34.489 --> 50:35.532
You're not going to do

50:37.325 --> 50:38.910
what I ask you to do anyway.

50:42.205 --> 50:44.291
I asked you to stay by his side.

50:46.126 --> 50:48.170
[melancholic music playing]

50:48.253 --> 50:49.629
I have a lot to say too.

50:52.090 --> 50:53.216
This grief

50:54.050 --> 50:55.844
can only be shared

50:57.554 --> 50:59.556
by you and me.

51:01.266 --> 51:02.476
In this world…

51:04.394 --> 51:05.687
there's no one else.

51:07.230 --> 51:08.774
[voice shaking] We should at least

51:10.233 --> 51:11.485
look out for each other

51:12.652 --> 51:14.446
and be honest about how we feel.

51:19.367 --> 51:20.410
[sighs deeply]

51:22.037 --> 51:23.121
Let's stay together today.

51:23.914 --> 51:25.123
At least for today.

51:25.749 --> 51:28.251
I won't be able to sleep
from the jet lag anyway,

51:28.335 --> 51:29.586
so let's catch up…

51:33.131 --> 51:34.591
[shudders, exhales]

51:36.426 --> 51:38.804
[sighs wearily] This is exactly
why I didn't want to come.

51:38.887 --> 51:41.598
[breathes heavily]

51:50.649 --> 51:51.650
[sighs]

51:53.151 --> 51:55.111
[music fades]

51:56.071 --> 51:57.239
[cellphone vibrates]

52:01.868 --> 52:03.620
[Tae-seo] <i>I'm on my way to Yeonwoo.</i>

52:03.703 --> 52:05.205
<i>My grandma suddenly collapsed.</i>

52:05.789 --> 52:08.667
<i>Hui-seo's not doing so well either,</i>
<i>so I'm going to stay with him.</i>

52:12.087 --> 52:13.255
[Eun-a]<i> Is she okay?</i>

52:15.632 --> 52:16.466
[sighs]

52:18.677 --> 52:19.678
[Tae-seo]<i> She has to be.</i>

52:20.846 --> 52:22.430
[gentle music playing]

52:22.514 --> 52:23.557
[So-hyeon] <i>This grief</i>

52:24.140 --> 52:25.684
can only be shared

52:25.767 --> 52:27.853
by you and me.

52:29.479 --> 52:30.647
Let's stay together today.

52:31.565 --> 52:32.816
At least for today.

52:34.150 --> 52:35.151
[sighs]

52:50.625 --> 52:52.627
[music swells]

52:59.593 --> 53:00.844
[So-hyeon] Eun-a, is that you?

53:15.066 --> 53:17.068
[music fades]

53:22.532 --> 53:23.366
[doctor] Hello.

53:24.784 --> 53:27.537
First off,
we've taken care of the bleeding.

53:27.621 --> 53:31.207
Given the patient's age,
recovery may take a bit longer.

53:31.291 --> 53:34.961
But the surgery went well,
so let's see how it goes.

53:35.712 --> 53:37.923
-All right, then.
-[Tae-seo] Thank you.

54:07.702 --> 54:08.536
Basically…

54:09.412 --> 54:12.999
Grandma wanted to send you
some of her <i>godeulppaegi</i> kimchi,

54:14.459 --> 54:16.962
and I wanted to lift her spirits
before the checkup.

54:17.045 --> 54:18.713
That's why I went…

54:19.881 --> 54:20.966
Good.

54:21.549 --> 54:23.551
It's about time you got out of Yeonwoo.

54:28.974 --> 54:31.559
It's purely psychological,
so be confident in yourself.

54:31.643 --> 54:34.229
You have strength in your leg,
so you'll be discharged in a week.

54:34.771 --> 54:36.064
You're perfectly healthy.

54:37.983 --> 54:39.275
It's swollen.

54:41.236 --> 54:43.279
Don't tell Grandma.

54:43.363 --> 54:45.115
It won't help with her recovery.

54:48.243 --> 54:51.079
Uh, and do that girl's frame for free.

54:51.830 --> 54:53.206
The girl who drove me here.

54:54.040 --> 54:55.250
I will.

55:04.968 --> 55:07.220
[A-sol over phone]
<i>I had some extra soft tofu stew,</i>

55:07.303 --> 55:08.471
<i>and I'm about to depart now.</i>

55:09.097 --> 55:10.265
<i>How did the surgery go?</i>

55:11.307 --> 55:12.434
It went well.

55:12.517 --> 55:14.310
[A-sol sighs]<i> What a relief.</i>

55:15.228 --> 55:18.356
<i>I kept imagining the worst,</i>
<i>so I couldn't even eat properly.</i>

55:18.440 --> 55:20.734
Mmm… Where are you right now?

55:28.992 --> 55:30.994
[gentle music playing]

55:43.590 --> 55:44.632
Grandpa.

55:45.842 --> 55:46.676
Hey.

55:51.473 --> 55:55.143
The person who drove Hui-seo here
is still in Gangneung.

55:55.894 --> 55:58.605
She's heading to Seoul now,
so I'm going to drive her back.

55:59.814 --> 56:01.649
Yeah, you should.

56:02.734 --> 56:04.277
Don't worry about things here.

56:08.073 --> 56:12.619
The surgery went well, so she'll be fine.

56:16.122 --> 56:18.041
I'll come right back tomorrow morning.

56:19.918 --> 56:21.669
Just rest at home.

56:21.753 --> 56:23.797
You'll be driving all night.

56:27.759 --> 56:29.010
No, I'll come.

56:41.564 --> 56:44.400
TAE-SEO, I'LL WAIT FOR YOU
KEEP ME UPDATED EVEN IF IT'S LATE

56:46.486 --> 56:51.241
[A-sol] I was wondering whether I should
stay the night and leave tomorrow.

56:52.992 --> 56:57.080
If you get short-term car insurance,
I can drive your car.

56:57.872 --> 57:00.416
Add me as the driver. I'll pay the fee.

57:01.000 --> 57:03.253
Oh. That's a thing?

57:08.049 --> 57:09.676
ONE-DAY CAR INSURANCE

57:09.759 --> 57:10.927
I found it.

57:11.594 --> 57:12.512
I'd be very grateful.

57:13.721 --> 57:15.181
I'm the one who's grateful.

57:16.432 --> 57:18.518
Hui-seo never really comes to my place.

57:21.062 --> 57:23.106
So that's where you live. Your place.

57:25.233 --> 57:27.944
It kicks in at midnight, so…

57:29.863 --> 57:31.406
Can we stay for ten more minutes?

57:32.740 --> 57:33.575
Sure.

57:39.497 --> 57:40.707
[cellphone vibrates]

57:43.501 --> 57:45.003
[Tae-seo] <i>The surgery went well.</i>

57:45.086 --> 57:48.798
<i>-You don't need to worry.</i>
-[Eun-a sighs in relief] <i>I knew it would.</i>

57:49.382 --> 57:50.842
<i>I know your grandma well.</i>

57:51.509 --> 57:52.886
<i>She's strong.</i>

57:55.013 --> 57:57.015
[cellphone vibrating]

58:00.310 --> 58:01.811
-Hey, Hyeong-seok.
-[Hyeong-seok] <i>Hey!</i>

58:02.353 --> 58:03.313
<i>Was the name tag…</i>

58:03.938 --> 58:05.273
<i>Was it Im Ji-sol?</i>

58:05.356 --> 58:10.695
If it was, you can't do that to me.
You should've told me.

58:10.778 --> 58:11.613
It wasn't.

58:11.696 --> 58:15.116
[Hyeong-seok] <i>I asked her out</i>
<i>and got completely humiliated.</i>

58:15.200 --> 58:16.659
<i>When I think about that time…</i>

58:16.743 --> 58:19.829
[exclaiming]

58:19.913 --> 58:21.581
It still makes me cringe.

58:21.664 --> 58:23.958
I must've been out of my mind back then.

58:24.876 --> 58:26.419
<i>Hey, hang up.</i>

58:26.503 --> 58:28.796
<i>I'm going to call Mi-ju.</i>

58:28.880 --> 58:30.965
-[Tae-seo] You do that. Bye.
-[camera shutter clicks]

58:34.761 --> 58:36.012
Im Ji-sol?

58:37.847 --> 58:39.140
Im Ji-sol…

58:47.899 --> 58:50.902
Ah… Im A-sol.

58:54.155 --> 58:55.156
[sighs]

59:04.791 --> 59:07.043
You can sleep the whole way there.

59:07.710 --> 59:10.255
-You must be exhausted.
-[seatbelt clicks]

59:10.338 --> 59:12.632
It's a long night drive,
so I should keep you company.

59:14.092 --> 59:16.219
Mmm, I'll drive to where you live.

59:16.302 --> 59:19.847
No, you can drive to yours.
My place isn't far from there.

59:20.932 --> 59:24.018
It'll be dawn when we get to Seoul.
You won't be able to find a cab.

59:26.771 --> 59:27.814
[A-sol yawns]

59:32.151 --> 59:33.152
Oh.

59:35.113 --> 59:36.823
[seatbelt clicks]

59:37.949 --> 59:39.951
-All right, let's go.
-Okay.

59:40.034 --> 59:41.160
[engine starts, revs]

59:47.625 --> 59:48.918
[A-sol] By the way…

59:51.129 --> 59:52.255
Weren't you asleep?

59:52.338 --> 59:53.506
Earlier…

59:54.132 --> 59:56.175
you said you'd drive to where I live.

59:56.759 --> 59:57.969
How did you know?

59:59.178 --> 01:00:00.722
When we first met,

01:00:01.931 --> 01:00:04.434
you went home while we were talking
to get the painting.

01:00:04.892 --> 01:00:05.727
Ah.

01:00:05.810 --> 01:00:07.854
You said it was five minutes
from where we met.

01:00:07.937 --> 01:00:09.230
Right.

01:00:09.314 --> 01:00:13.526
And you're the only person who's allowed
takeout at the restaurant with my frame.

01:00:14.152 --> 01:00:16.446
And you studied
at Hyeong-seok's study center.

01:00:16.529 --> 01:00:18.573
[amusing music playing]

01:00:25.121 --> 01:00:27.081
My name tag's in Yeonwoo, isn't it?

01:00:27.749 --> 01:00:31.210
Oh… No wonder I felt drawn to that place.

01:00:33.171 --> 01:00:34.631
Then, let's be friends from now on.

01:00:35.340 --> 01:00:37.383
-You don't mind, right?
-Well…

01:00:37.967 --> 01:00:39.886
[A-sol] Okay, we've cleared that up.

01:00:39.969 --> 01:00:42.347
Anything you want to ask me
about the past?

01:00:42.430 --> 01:00:44.515
-You can go ahead.
-I don't.

01:00:46.851 --> 01:00:48.853
Go to sleep, Ms. Im. We'll be a while.

01:00:48.936 --> 01:00:51.606
[inhales] I said we should be friends.

01:00:55.818 --> 01:00:56.819
Sleep.

01:01:09.248 --> 01:01:10.500
[cellphone vibrating]

01:01:16.673 --> 01:01:18.299
SEONG-CHAN

01:01:28.643 --> 01:01:30.937
You know how to get home from here, right?

01:01:47.036 --> 01:01:51.249
[So-hyeon] I came because I missed her,
but maybe I shouldn't have come.

01:01:51.332 --> 01:01:52.333
[Seong-chan] How's Eun-a?

01:01:54.544 --> 01:01:55.753
[So-hyeon] It's just upsetting

01:01:56.337 --> 01:02:00.091
to see her struggling alone
in an empty guesthouse.

01:02:44.302 --> 01:02:46.471
[emotional music playing]

01:03:15.917 --> 01:03:16.918
[cellphone vibrates]

01:03:23.299 --> 01:03:24.425
[Eun-a] <i>Get away from there.</i>

01:03:47.615 --> 01:03:49.617
[music fades]

01:03:50.117 --> 01:03:53.621
STILL SHINING

01:03:53.704 --> 01:03:55.706
[melancholic music playing]

01:04:19.564 --> 01:04:21.983
[Seong-chan] <i>You put so much</i>
<i>care and effort into that place.</i>

01:04:22.066 --> 01:04:25.278
Now you can have it all back.
What exactly is the problem?

01:04:25.862 --> 01:04:29.824
[Tae-seo]<i> Does that Seong-chan guy</i>
<i>have something to do with your guesthouse?</i>

01:04:30.616 --> 01:04:32.159
[Eun-a] <i>I'm not in Seoul.</i>

01:04:32.243 --> 01:04:34.495
[Tae-seo]<i> Missing each other,</i>
<i>being drained emotionally…</i>

01:04:34.579 --> 01:04:36.289
[Eun-a] <i>I'll explain everything in person.</i>

01:04:36.372 --> 01:04:38.457
We were talking about our future
just the other day.

01:04:38.541 --> 01:04:40.793
[Eun-a]<i> I have to make it back today.</i>

01:04:40.877 --> 01:04:42.670
[Tae-seo]
<i>In the past decade of Eun-a's life,</i>

01:04:44.672 --> 01:04:45.882
<i>he was the only one present.</i>

01:04:52.430 --> 01:04:54.432
Subtitle translation by: Hyesoo Lee
